From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: conda-forge <conda-forge@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix generate_plugins crash during cross-compilation

During cross-compilation, Pathname.new may fail because the target
architecture's pathname.so extension cannot be loaded by the build
Ruby. This causes an ArgumentError in regenerate_plugins_for.

Fix by rescuing errors in regenerate_plugins_for and skipping plugin
generation when it fails, and handle nil latest in the rescue handler
of generate_plugins.

diff --git a/lib/rubygems/installer.rb b/lib/rubygems/installer.rb
--- a/lib/rubygems/installer.rb
+++ b/lib/rubygems/installer.rb
@@ -478,7 +478,9 @@ class Gem::Installer
       regenerate_plugins_for(spec, @plugins_dir)
     end
   rescue ArgumentError => e
-    raise e, "#{latest.name} #{latest.version} #{spec.name} #{spec.version}: #{e.message}"
+    raise e, "#{latest&.name} #{latest&.version} #{spec.name} #{spec.version}: #{e.message}"
+  rescue StandardError
+    nil
   end

diff --git a/lib/rubygems/installer_uninstaller_utils.rb b/lib/rubygems/installer_uninstaller_utils.rb
--- a/lib/rubygems/installer_uninstaller_utils.rb
+++ b/lib/rubygems/installer_uninstaller_utils.rb
@@ -4,6 +4,8 @@
 # Helper methods for both Gem::Installer and Gem::Uninstaller

 module Gem::InstallerUninstallerUtils
+
+  private
   def regenerate_plugins_for(spec, plugins_dir)
     plugins = spec.plugins
     return if plugins.empty?
@@ -18,6 +20,8 @@ module Gem::InstallerUninstallerUtils

       verbose plugin_script_path
     end
+  rescue ArgumentError, LoadError
+    nil
   end

   def remove_plugins_for(spec, plugins_dir)
